start.label: pruritic urticarial papules and plaques of pregnancy

examples.en: The baby has a skin rash.
I break out in a rash if I eat shellfish.
He developed a rash.
Don't get stampeded into any rash decisions.
I rashly agreed to look after the children.
The insect bite produced a rash.
It was rash of you to make that promise.
Don't be rash about this decision. Take your time.
Please Jessie, don't do anything rash.
She had a nasty rash on her arm.
If I eat eggs, I come out in a rash.
The rash has finally cleared.
I broke out in a painful rash.
Most babies get nappy rash at some stage.
A rash business decision left him $600 in debt.
Any foods containing wheat bring him out in a rash.
One important diagnostic feature of this condition is a mild rash.
I had a terrible rash on my face, and I felt like a freak.
It was a rash decision, and it lost him the race (=caused him to lose the race).
Do something rash that he will forever repent.
The doctor prescribed a new cream for the rash.
My mother comes out in a rash if she eats seafood.
The poor baby has a rash all over his little bottom.
The usual symptoms are a pink rash with a slight fever.
The town has suffered a rash of arsons.
The town has suffered a rash of arson attacks.
Symptoms of the disease include rash and fever.
It was rather rash of you to lend them your car.
Don't go making any rash decisions about your future!
There's been a rash of car thefts in the city centre.
